@NODE StartingProg "Starting Version Handler"
@TOC UsingProgram
@{LINDENT 1}

@{b}Starting Version Handler@{ub}



This program may be started from the Workbench or the Shell window.


This program will detach from the Shell so you need not use Run or any other
variant.  There are a few command line arguments you may use when loading:



@{b}PROJECT/K@{ub}

Project to manipulate.

ex: VersionHandler PROJECT "Version Handler"


@{b}AUTOBUMP/S@{ub}

Auto-Bump versions, dates and time.


@{b}VERSION/S@{ub}

Bump version and revision.


@{b}DATE/S@{ub}

Bump dates.


@{b}TIME/S@{ub}

Bump time.


@{b}ICONIFY/S@{ub}

Start in iconified mode.


@{b}ICON_X/K@{ub}

X coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}ICON_Y/K@{ub}

Y coordinate for AppIcon.


@{b}PUBSCREEN/K@{ub}

Name of public screen to open the interface on.


@{b}LANGUAGE/K@{ub}

Preferred locale strings language.

Language must be all lower case.


@{b}UI/K@{ub}

Open or keep the user interface closed.

UI=TRUE or UI=FALSE.


@{b}NOVERSION/S@{ub}

Do not display program title when not using the editor.


@{b}DONOTDETACH/S@{ub}

Do not detach from the Shell.



The arguments are not case sensitive and may be mixed in any order.

ex: VersionHandler PROJECT "Version Handler" AUTOBUMP


Only one copy may be run at one time.  You will be notified if more than one
copy is attempted to be executed.


